==English==
===Pronunciation===

:so' da lite

===Etymology===

:Named for the alkaline silicate composition.

===Noun===
'''Sodalite'''

#A [[mineral]] of alkaline [[igneous]] and [[plutonic]] [[rock]]s that are low in [[silica]]. Pink Sodalite is sometimes called ''Hackmanite''. Sodalite and [[Lazurite]] form the ''Sodalite Group'' of silicate minerals.

=== Chemical composition ===
*Sodium aluminum silicate with chlorine, <math>Na_4Al_3Si_3O_{12}Cl</math>
 
=== Physical properties ===

*Moh's Hardness: 5.5-6.0
*Specific gravity: 2.2-2.3
*Color: White, blue, violet, pink, colorless
*Luster: Glassy, transparent to translucent
*Fracture: Conchoidal to uneven
*Cleavage: Poor dodecahedral
*Habit: Cubic-hexoctahedral

===Special test===

:Frequently fluorescent yellow to orange in long-wave ultraviolet

